pesticide.PPE: chemical resistant gloves, long-sleeved shirt, long pants, shoes plus socks

Active_Ingredients.name: LCO MOR116
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Stimulates root growth and nodulation, promotes mycorrhizal symbiosis

Active_Ingredients.name: Bradyrhizobium japonicum
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Forms root nodules for nitrogen fixation

Safety_Information.general_Info: Wash hands thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco or using the toilet. Users should remove contaminated clothing/PPE immediately if pesticide gets inside. Then wash thoroughly and put on clean clothing.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing eye.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: In case of an emergency involving this product, call day or night 1-800-424-9300 for medical assistance.
